  Corresponding source: the complete corresponding source for the bundled
  FFmpeg (version 8.1) is available from https://ffmpeg.org/download.html.
  Written offer: for three (3) years from distribution you may also obtain it
  by opening an issue at https://github.com/lifebugz/easyclip; it will be
  provided (or a download location given) at no more than the cost of
  distribution. The exact builds and SHA-256 checksums are pinned in
  scripts/ffmpeg-checksums.json. Upstream build sources:
    - macOS:   https://ffmpeg.martin-riedl.de/
    - Windows: BtbN LGPL builds (https://github.com/BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds), pinned
               and mirrored at https://github.com/lifebugz/easyclip/releases

  LGPL relink/replace right: because FFmpeg is shipped as a SEPARATE
  executable, you may use a modified FFmpeg by replacing the sidecar binary
  at src-tauri/binaries/ffmpeg-<target-triple> (or the corresponding file
  inside the installed application bundle) with your own LGPL-compatible build.

